					<source>Background task guidance</source>
				</segment>
			</unit>
			<unit id="108" translate="yes">
				<segment state="initial">
					<source>Consider the following guidance when developing your background task, and before publishing your app.</source>
				</segment>
			</unit>
			<unit id="109" translate="yes">
				<segment state="initial">
					<source>**CPU quotas:  **Background tasks are limited by the amount of wall-clock usage time they get based on trigger type.</source>
				</segment>
			</unit>
			<unit id="110" translate="yes">
				<segment state="initial">
					<source>Most triggers are limited to 30 seconds of wall-clock usage, while some have the ability to run up to 10 minutes in order to complete intensive tasks.</source>
				</segment>
			</unit>
			<unit id="111" translate="yes">
				<segment state="initial">
					<source>Background tasks should be lightweight to save battery life and provide a better user experience for foreground apps.</source>
				</segment>
			</unit>
			<unit id="112" translate="yes">
				<originalData>
